      "form_guide": "",
      "comment": "EXPEDITE (2) rocketed out of the inside draw with a strong early sectional and gave a sight but had to settle for a placing, finishing third (26.18) at Geelong over 460m. Got the money at his only try from this box. Can find winning form. INSPECTION (6) looks close to another win after hitting the frame in a 2.5 lengths second (30.42) in a Grade 7 at this track. The form out of last race has been strong. Must be included in calculations. REINDEER KEITH (1) continues to race well but is struggling to break through, placing at his last four runs. Last time finished 2nd in a Mix 6/7 FIN on March 7 over 525m at this track behind Uncle Stiltskin beaten 8 lengths (30.62). Expecting another good run. KOPACKI RIT (8) deserves plenty of thought at his first run at this circuit.",
